01:14:52,420 --> 01:14:55,355
Tell Vikram and Benoy
that I said "Hi", okay?

827
01:14:55,490 --> 01:14:57,424
I will... and you take care...

828
01:14:57,492 --> 01:14:58,550
I will.

829
01:14:58,627 --> 01:15:00,356
- And keep calling...
- I will...

830
01:15:00,428 --> 01:15:01,656
Okay, bye...

831
01:15:13,975 --> 01:15:15,909
- Chotu.
- Brother...

832
01:16:14,502 --> 01:16:16,163
Bhairav Singh

833
01:16:17,572 --> 01:16:19,062
I am coming to get you...

834
01:16:21,443 --> 01:16:23,502
Do you understand recession?

835
01:16:24,045 --> 01:16:25,512
Disgraceful.

836
01:16:56,011 --> 01:16:57,205
Was this picnic your idea?

837
01:16:58,546 --> 01:17:01,071
Your father isn't as bad
as you make him out to be.

838
01:17:01,950 --> 01:17:05,784
I just don't get him.
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

839
01:17:07,555 --> 01:17:09,750
Spoken like a true writer...

840
01:17:10,825 --> 01:17:12,087
I'm not talking like a writer...

841
01:17:12,827 --> 01:17:16,160
Your mother would have been
proud if she were alive today.

842
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:18,563
She always wanted you
to be a writer.

843
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:20,094
- Really?
- Yes.

844
01:17:21,169 --> 01:17:24,627
She never told your father,
but she told me...

845
01:17:25,573 --> 01:17:30,510
How she would have loved that line...
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

846
01:17:33,181 --> 01:17:37,845
Sometimes a demon,
sometimes a lamb.

847
01:17:37,919 --> 01:17:40,581
Stop it!

848
01:17:49,731 --> 01:17:53,132
I have an idea...

849
01:17:53,201 --> 01:17:55,192
What is it?

850
01:17:57,706 --> 01:17:59,037
Let's hear one of Rohan's poems...

851
01:18:03,878 --> 01:18:05,743
He's written a full-length novel...

852
01:18:07,215 --> 01:18:10,275
I'm not asking you to
change your mind...

853
01:18:10,885 --> 01:18:14,218
Listen to it.
If you don't like it, don't applaud.

854
01:18:17,759 --> 01:18:19,886
Come on, big man.
Go for it.

855
01:18:24,232 --> 01:18:29,226
If you could see past the shore,
you would know what I am thinking.

856
01:18:30,171 --> 01:18:34,904
If you could hear the waves,
you would know what I am thinking.

857
01:18:36,044 --> 01:18:40,845
Remove your veil of obstinacy,
and look beyond the window.

858
01:18:41,783 --> 01:18:46,311
If you could see through convention,
you would know what I am thinking.

859
01:18:47,589 --> 01:18:52,617
If you had faith in yourself as I do,
you could walk with me a while...

860
01:18:53,661 --> 01:18:58,155
If you could see the colours as I do,
you could walk with me a while.

861
01:18:59,200 --> 01:19:01,600
If you want to touch the sky as I do,

862
01:19:01,669 --> 01:19:03,899
then your desires would come true.

863
01:19:04,672 --> 01:19:09,336
Then, in my next life,
we could fly together a while.

864
01:19:17,152 --> 01:19:18,210
Forget it.

865
01:19:19,220 --> 01:19:20,619
Only a woman's magazine will publish it...

866
01:19:20,688 --> 01:19:22,986
...or someone will drop a
coin in your begging bowl.

867
01:20:11,606 --> 01:20:12,664
Hello.

868
01:20:15,710 --> 01:20:16,768
Please... Sit...

869
01:20:17,412 --> 01:20:18,470
Hello.

870
01:20:18,546 --> 01:20:19,604
- How are you?
- Please, have a seat.

871
01:20:19,680 --> 01:20:20,738
How was the journey?

872
01:20:21,082 --> 01:20:23,050
Okay, our flight got a bit delayed.

873
01:20:24,619 --> 01:20:26,143
I made these for you to read.

874
01:20:50,111 --> 01:20:54,844
They're good...

875
01:20:56,050 --> 01:20:57,745
I'm glad you came today.

876
01:20:58,786 --> 01:21:00,117
I'm off to Kolkata tomorrow...

877
01:21:00,588 --> 01:21:03,182
Let me show you the workshop.

878
01:21:03,991 --> 01:21:05,049
Sure.

879
01:21:10,598 --> 01:21:11,656
Hello?

880
01:21:11,732 --> 01:21:13,199
- Is that Mr. Singh?
- Yes?

881
01:21:13,534 --> 01:21:16,901
I'm Mrs Batra here,
Principal of Arjun's school.

882
01:21:16,971 --> 01:21:18,529
Yes Mrs Batra, tell me.

883
01:21:18,606 --> 01:21:21,734
There's been another problem with
your son, Arjun, this morning...

884
01:21:22,543 --> 01:21:25,512
You know? We'd like you to come here
and take him back home today.

885
01:21:26,747 --> 01:21:29,739
I'm in a meeting right now.
Can I come after lunch?

886
01:21:30,017 --> 01:21:32,815
No Mr. Singh. This is an
extremely serious problem.

887
01:21:32,887 --> 01:21:33,979
I know Mrs. Batra but...

888
01:21:35,089 --> 01:21:36,852
Keep him in your office for some time.

889
01:21:36,924 --> 01:21:38,482
Mr. Singh please understand.

890
01:21:38,559 --> 01:21:40,823
I cannot allow Arjun to
remain in school today.

891
01:21:41,829 --> 01:21:44,093
Okay, I'm coming.

892
01:21:44,165 --> 01:21:45,223
In half an hour?

893
01:21:45,299 --> 01:21:46,630
Yes Mrs. Batra. I'm coming right now.

894
01:21:46,701 --> 01:21:47,759
Thank you, Mr. Singh.

895
01:21:51,105 --> 01:21:55,235
I'm sorry, but I have to
rush to my son's school.

896
01:21:55,576 --> 01:21:58,909
He's been unwell
recently and it got worse today.

897
01:21:58,980 --> 01:22:02,848
But Mr. Rao will show
you around the workshop.

898
01:22:02,917 --> 01:22:05,579
No problem. We'll come back tomorrow.

899
01:22:05,653 --> 01:22:07,917
We have other factories to see today.

900
01:22:08,055 --> 01:22:11,752
But I told you, I have to be in
Kolkata tomorrow. I've committed it.

901
01:22:12,193 --> 01:22:14,252
I am sorry. We can't stay any longer.

902
01:22:15,129 --> 01:22:18,155
Anyway. We'll meet again.
Some other time?

903
01:22:18,866 --> 01:22:19,924
Okay...

904
01:22:20,134 --> 01:22:21,192
Let's go.

905
01:22:51,632 --> 01:22:52,690
What happened?

906
01:22:52,900 --> 01:22:53,958
Get in the car.

907
01:23:13,120 --> 01:23:14,178
What happened?

908
01:23:15,590 --> 01:23:16,750
His blood pressure is very low.

909
01:23:17,258 --> 01:23:19,158
Seems like he's had a bad fall.

910
01:23:19,927 --> 01:23:21,224
There could be internal bleeding.

911
01:23:22,063 --> 01:23:24,964
I'll have to check. We'll keep him
under observation for a few days.

912
01:23:25,032 --> 01:23:26,090
How many days?

913
01:23:26,667 --> 01:23:27,725
Four to five days.

914
01:23:27,802 --> 01:23:28,860
Four to five days?

915
01:23:28,936 --> 01:23:31,962
Don't worry. He'll
be fine. Don't worry.

916
01:23:32,873 --> 01:23:33,931
Thank you.

917
01:23:37,612 --> 01:23:38,670
How did it happen?

918
01:23:39,213 --> 01:23:40,271
Fell down the stairs.

919
01:23:41,682 --> 01:23:42,740
How?

920
01:23:43,150 --> 01:23:45,675
How should I know? He just fell.

921
01:23:49,957 --> 01:23:51,356
You go home. I'll stay here.

922
01:23:52,693 --> 01:23:53,751
I'm also staying.

923
01:23:58,299 --> 01:23:59,357
What happened to your results?

924
01:24:00,635 --> 01:24:02,364
- I passed.
- Marks?

925
01:24:03,704 --> 01:24:05,763
- They're good.
- Good.

926
01:24:14,248 --> 01:24:15,840
I'm going to Kolkata for three days.

927
01:24:17,985 --> 01:24:20,886
If all goes well,
I'll return with a few contracts.

928
01:24:21,989 --> 01:24:23,889
You stay here with Arjun.

929
01:24:24,191 --> 01:24:26,716
And don't leave him alone, okay?

930
01:24:26,794 --> 01:24:27,852
Yes Sir.

931
01:24:33,200 --> 01:24:34,258
And...

932
01:24:34,802 --> 01:24:36,861
No need to inform Uncle and Auntie.

933
01:24:38,005 --> 01:24:41,406
I've told them that both of
you are going with me, okay?

934
01:24:41,742 --> 01:24:42,800
Yes Sir.

935
01:24:45,146 --> 01:24:46,204
Fine.

936
01:24:56,023 --> 01:24:57,081
Have you eaten?

937
01:25:04,365 --> 01:25:05,764
Sir has gone to Kolkata.

938
01:25:08,302 --> 01:25:09,360
Aren't you happy?

939
01:25:17,912 --> 01:25:18,970
What happened yesterday?

940
01:25:48,008 --> 01:25:49,066
For you.

941
01:25:56,751 --> 01:25:57,809
And these...

942
01:25:57,885 --> 01:25:59,477
If you feel like reading.

943
01:26:07,962 --> 01:26:10,362
This has my poems and stories.

944
01:26:11,031 --> 01:26:12,089
Would you like to hear some?

945
01:26:16,370 --> 01:26:17,428
Hello Arjun.

946
01:26:19,173 --> 01:26:20,299
Are you feeling well today?

947
01:26:21,008 --> 01:26:22,066
Good.

948
01:26:28,048 --> 01:26:29,310
Could you change his clothes?

949
01:26:29,383 --> 01:26:30,850
- Yes.
- Thank you.

950
01:26:35,389 --> 01:26:36,447
What is it?

951
01:27:05,820 --> 01:27:06,878
What now?

952
01:28:05,880 --> 01:28:10,874
Lunch was to be served by 12:30!
Its 1:00 p.m now!

953
01:28:10,951 --> 01:28:12,885
Please don't shout.
It's bad for you.

954
01:28:12,953 --> 01:28:14,181
Yes I know.

955
01:28:14,488 --> 01:28:15,887
I can get a heart attack.

956
01:28:15,956 --> 01:28:18,049
But what if I die of hunger before that?

957
01:28:18,125 --> 01:28:20,184
I'll go and get your food now.

958
01:28:20,628 --> 01:28:21,890
Get it fast...

959
01:28:22,429 --> 01:28:24,624
Corpses don't eat.

960
01:28:29,503 --> 01:28:30,629
Why don't you laugh?

961
01:28:32,106 --> 01:28:33,232
I am 80 years old...

962
01:28:34,241 --> 01:28:35,640
Grandfather of six.

963
01:28:36,143 --> 01:28:37,440
Great grandfather of two...

964
01:28:37,912 --> 01:28:38,970
Can't I shout?

965
01:28:39,914 --> 01:28:40,972
Laugh.

966
01:28:41,916 --> 01:28:42,974
Laugh.

967
01:28:58,365 --> 01:28:59,423
Would you like to listen to a poem?

968
01:29:10,544 --> 01:29:11,602
Chandu's Cycle.

969
01:29:12,479 --> 01:29:14,947
Chandu's cycle was
just like Chandu...

970
01:29:15,549 --> 01:29:18,416
As it moved, it crickered and
crankered, just like Chandu.

971
01:29:19,286 --> 01:29:22,346
The handle was as light
as Chandu's slender hand.

972
01:29:22,957 --> 01:29:25,983
The pedals were as thin
as Chandu's spindle legs.

973
01:29:26,961 --> 01:29:29,953
The seat was as broad
as Chandu's huge buttocks.

974
01:29:30,698 --> 01:29:33,963
The carrier was as small
as Chandu's short career.

975
01:29:34,501 --> 01:29:36,093
Yet, it was Chandu's true friend.

976
01:29:36,570 --> 01:29:38,003
It was always loyal to Chandu.

977
01:29:38,973 --> 01:29:42,500
It took Chandu's heavy weight with ease.

978
01:29:43,077 --> 01:29:46,513
One day the cycle broke down.

979
01:29:46,981 --> 01:29:48,972
Seeing a bull charging at him,

980
01:29:49,083 --> 01:29:50,414
Chandu dropped it hard.

981
01:29:50,985 --> 01:29:53,977
When Monty Mechanic
could not save the cycle,

982
01:29:54,655 --> 01:29:57,988
Chandu's father sold
it to a scrap dealer.

983
01:29:58,459 --> 01:30:01,986
Chandu drowned himself in his books.

984
01:30:02,129 --> 01:30:05,098
Like he had an old dream to fulfill.

985
01:30:05,733 --> 01:30:07,132
Later, when Chandu grew up,

986
01:30:07,534 --> 01:30:09,001
He used his very first salary...

987
01:30:09,403 --> 01:30:12,998
And got himself a new cycle...

988
01:30:14,008 --> 01:30:15,066
But...

989
01:30:15,242 --> 01:30:16,300
But?

990
01:30:16,543 --> 01:30:20,001
This cycle too was
just like Chandu...

991
01:30:20,347 --> 01:30:23,009
It still crickered and
crankered as it moved around.

992
01:30:23,550 --> 01:30:25,017
It's seat was...

993
01:30:25,085 --> 01:30:27,144
As broad as Chandu's huge buttocks.

994
01:30:27,354 --> 01:30:29,015
The carrier was as small...

995
01:30:29,089 --> 01:30:31,023
as Chandu's short career.

996
01:30:34,028 --> 01:30:35,086
You wrote that?

997
01:30:36,263 --> 01:30:38,026
- Yes
- Wow...

998
01:30:38,699 --> 01:30:39,757
Very good.

999
01:30:40,634 --> 01:30:42,033
Very inspiring!

1000
01:30:42,269 --> 01:30:44,703
- Thank you.
- Keep writing like this, son.

1001
01:30:45,439 --> 01:30:46,770
Keep writing.

1002
01:30:48,108 --> 01:30:50,702
Write.

1003
01:30:59,653 --> 01:31:02,645
How many friends do
you have in school?

1004
01:31:06,060 --> 01:31:07,118
Seven.

1005
01:31:07,194 --> 01:31:08,252
Their names?

1006
01:31:08,462 --> 01:31:09,520
Apurva,

1007
01:31:10,064 --> 01:31:11,463
Sunny, Raju,

1008
01:31:11,532 --> 01:31:13,056
Batuk, Kunal...

1009
01:31:13,300 --> 01:31:15,234
Kunal..., Kunal...,

1010
01:31:15,302 --> 01:31:16,360
Veer.

1011
01:31:17,071 --> 01:31:18,129
And?

1012
01:31:18,338 --> 01:31:19,396
And...

1013
01:31:20,607 --> 01:31:21,665
That's only six.

1014
01:31:24,078 --> 01:31:25,272
And one more...

1015
01:31:26,547 --> 01:31:27,605
Tushar.

1016
01:31:28,082 --> 01:31:29,413
You have so many friends.

1017
01:31:30,084 --> 01:31:31,278
I have only three.

1018
01:31:32,619 --> 01:31:34,143
What was your mother like?

1019
01:31:35,089 --> 01:31:37,455
My mother was very nice.

1020
01:31:38,692 --> 01:31:40,159
She loved me a lot.

1021
01:31:41,095 --> 01:31:42,323
She smelled wonderful,

1022
01:31:42,396 --> 01:31:44,091
when I'd cuddle up to sleep.

1023
01:31:44,765 --> 01:31:46,096
Just like a mother.

1024
01:31:48,202 --> 01:31:50,170
I don't know what
my mother was like.

1025
01:31:50,771 --> 01:31:52,102
Do you know her?

1026
01:31:53,707 --> 01:31:54,765
No.

1027
01:32:02,449 --> 01:32:03,507
Mr Poet...

1028
01:32:06,120 --> 01:32:07,348
Why don't you ever laugh?

1029
01:32:08,722 --> 01:32:09,780
Yes.

1030
01:32:09,857 --> 01:32:12,121
Look at you now. You look so good.

1031
01:32:13,727 --> 01:32:15,126
When do we hear something new?

1032
01:32:15,429 --> 01:32:16,487
Tonight?

1033
01:32:16,663 --> 01:32:17,721
In the night?

1034
01:32:18,465 --> 01:32:19,727
Do you also write at night?

1035
01:32:20,134 --> 01:32:21,192
Sometimes.

1036
01:32:21,268 --> 01:32:22,394
Beware of the night...

1037
01:32:23,203 --> 01:32:24,261
You see...

1038
01:32:24,605 --> 01:32:26,129
The day destroys the night.

1039
01:32:26,473 --> 01:32:27,735
Night divides the day.

1040
01:32:28,308 --> 01:32:29,366
Try to run.

1041
01:32:29,676 --> 01:32:30,734
Try to hide...

1042
01:32:30,878 --> 01:32:32,277
Break on through to the other side.

1043
01:32:35,215 --> 01:32:38,150
This is the true
story of three friends...

1044
01:32:38,418 --> 01:32:41,148
Muninder, Benoy and Rohit.

1045
01:32:41,522 --> 01:32:45,151
The kingdom where they lived,

1046
01:32:45,225 --> 01:32:47,159
would choose the smartest boys
for training.

1047
01:32:47,494 --> 01:32:51,760
Years later, they would join
the King's prestigious army.

1048
01:32:52,432 --> 01:32:56,163
But nobody really knew what
went on inside the castle.

1049
01:32:56,703 --> 01:33:00,161
Their parents didn't know
that the King's evil minister,

1050
01:33:00,240 --> 01:33:03,607
was brain-washing the kids
and turning them into robots.

1051
01:33:03,911 --> 01:33:05,173
Is it a true story?

1052
01:33:05,245 --> 01:33:06,303
Yes.

1053
01:33:06,380 --> 01:33:09,178
The wicked man's name was Rathod.

1054
01:33:09,249 --> 01:33:10,307
Rathod!

1055
01:33:10,384 --> 01:33:11,578
Yes, Rathod.

1056
01:34:15,782 --> 01:34:17,875
Vikreet and Benoy were
with the full Robot Army...

1057
01:34:18,252 --> 01:34:20,243
Muninder and the kids
were due any minute now...

1058
01:34:20,554 --> 01:34:23,546
Rohit was worried.
They hadn't come yet.

1059
01:34:23,991 --> 01:34:28,257
He turned around. And froze.
A terrified look came into his eyes.

1060
01:34:28,929 --> 01:34:30,920
He saw someone
coming through the tunnel.

1061
01:34:31,598 --> 01:34:33,395
Someone was coming from the tunnel...

1062
01:34:33,467 --> 01:34:34,593
Who was coming?

1063
01:34:38,505 --> 01:34:39,938
Who was it?

1064
01:34:45,879 --> 01:34:47,904
- We'll finish tomorrow...
- Now!

1065
01:34:54,621 --> 01:34:55,747
34 in Chemistry.

1066
01:34:57,291 --> 01:34:59,418
20 in Physics. 15 in Maths.

1067
01:35:00,761 --> 01:35:02,285
You told me you passed.

1068
01:35:03,897 --> 01:35:07,958
Is this a joke to you?

1069
01:35:09,369 --> 01:35:12,304
I thought you'd finally
become serious about your studies.

1070
01:35:12,372 --> 01:35:16,832
You're narrating
stories to half-dead people.

1071
01:35:16,910 --> 01:35:19,309
Just to hear them tell you
what a good writer you are?

1072
01:35:20,314 --> 01:35:21,372
What are you staring at?

1073
01:35:22,316 --> 01:35:23,374
Lower your eyes.

1074
01:35:24,718 --> 01:35:26,982
If this wasn't a hospital,
I would skin you right now.

1075
01:35:28,322 --> 01:35:31,314
I'm not going to
forget this in a hurry.

1076
01:35:32,626 --> 01:35:36,562
Come home. I'll make
sure I get an answer.

1077
01:35:44,004 --> 01:35:45,335
What did Sir say?

1078
01:35:45,472 --> 01:35:48,339
Sir said that he will send
me to the hospital as well.

1079
01:35:48,475 --> 01:35:49,533
Why?

1080
01:35:50,410 --> 01:35:51,536
Because I failed my exams.

1081
01:35:53,046 --> 01:35:55,344
So you'll go back to
boarding school?

1082
01:35:55,882 --> 01:35:56,940
No. Why?

1083
01:35:57,017 --> 01:36:01,647
Sir said if I don't pass,
he'll send me to a boarding school.

1084
01:37:19,433 --> 01:37:20,764
What happened that day?

1085
01:37:22,102 --> 01:37:23,433
Sir hit me.

1086
01:37:25,439 --> 01:37:26,497
Why?

1087
01:37:26,573 --> 01:37:31,033
Two boys were teasing me at school.
I broke one's teeth.

1088
01:37:33,447 --> 01:37:34,505
Did he beat you a lot?

1089
01:37:34,581 --> 01:37:36,446
He beat me with a belt.

1090
01:38:31,972 --> 01:38:33,030
Shall we go?

1091
01:38:48,188 --> 01:38:49,519
How old are you?

1092
01:38:57,697 --> 01:38:59,221
I'm asking you something.

1093
01:39:00,133 --> 01:39:01,191
How old are you?

1094
01:39:03,537 --> 01:39:04,595
Seventeen.

1095
01:39:05,539 --> 01:39:06,597
